comments: Sexton (UTA) steps into Wagner's (ORL) path to defend the throw-in and the contact is marginal.
George (UTA) touches the ball last before going out of bounds.
Carter Jr. (ORL) firms up in a screening position in Sexton's (UTA) path on his left foot.
George (UTA) places a hand on Suggs' (ORL) body as he releases away from the contact and Suggs' momentum carries him forwards.
Harris (ORL) briefly places both hands on Clarkson (UTA) as he establishes a screening position.
Wagner (ORL) makes clean contact with the ball, which causes Clarkson (UTA) to lose possession.
Clarkson (UTA) reaches in and initiates some contact with Wagner's (ORL) wrist, but Wagner maintains possession out in transition.
Suggs (ORL) lowers his arm and initiates contact with Collins' (UTA) forearm, affecting his driving shot attempt.
Collins (UTA) is the first to touch his own shot attempt after it does not touch the rim.
Collins (UTA) commits a take foul on Banchero (ORL).
Collins (UTA) and Carter Jr. (ORL) come together in pursuit of the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Collins (UTA) commits a take foul on Suggs (ORL).
Suggs (ORL) avoids making contact with George's (UTA) arm as he defends the driving shot attempt.  The ball goes off of the bottom of the backboard, which causes George to lose control of the ball.
